&lt;li&gt;Use our LA studio on a regular cadence to keep production moving, plus occasional travel for creator and influencer shoots&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flex to support the Creative Strategy team on emerging brands and LTO launches, filming ahead of packaging drops so the CS team can move fast right after&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a working content budget for props, collaborators, and whatever a shoot needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has 3-5 years producing content in UGC or paid social (brand, agency, creator, or freelance) with a portfolio that proves it performed, not just that it looked good&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is genuinely comfortable being the face of the brand, on camera, regularly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edits fluently in CapCut, Premiere Pro, or DaVinci Resolve, and can mock up static creative in Figma, Canva, or Photoshop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understands what makes content stop the scroll, and speaks the language of hook rate, hold rate, CTR, and nCAC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can take a concept handed to them in the morning and turn around a launch-ready ad the same day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is based in or near the LA/SoCal area (or willing to relocate) and can commit to regular studio days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of the difference between &quot;brand&quot; creative and content that actually converts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AI creative tools (Higgsfield, Butter, Nano Banana, Sora, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A portfolio or reel that makes us want to hire you before we finish scrolling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You know what CTR, hook rate, and hold rate mean — and you think about them while you edit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health, wellness, or supplement experie

