&lt;li&gt;Has owned packaging from concept to approval to launch, and can point to specific projects where they were the primary accountable person if something went wrong&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has managed a high volume of simultaneous launches, not just a handful. Experience with beauty, personal care, food, or wellness CPG is welcome. If it lives on a Whole Foods shelf, the skills translate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has a track record of managing external vendors and suppliers through full project cycles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings strong cross-functional project management skills and is comfortable driving alignment across teams they don&#39;t control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is proficient in Asana or a comparable project management tool&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Approach to the role:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking ownership - not just of tasks, but of outcomes. You don&#39;t wait to be told something is off. You catch it, you fix it, you close the loop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operating in ambiguity without losing momentum. We don&#39;t have a process for everything and we never will. That&#39;s not a problem for you - it&#39;s where you do your best work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mo

